JOHANNESBURG Activities at Tshwane University of Technology s (TUT) Pretoria Campus will resume on Monday after a protest last week.TUT said examinations will continue as scheduled. Take note that the Pretoria Campus is accessible and examinations are continuing as scheduled pic.twitter.com/D04dMjrbgl Examinations will commence on Monday, 29 May 2017, as scheduled. A contingency plan is in place to safeguard students, staff, examinations and exam venues, TUT said in a statement.READ: TUT suspends classes amid strike by outsourced workersActivities at the university s other campuses will also continue as scheduled.The university was hit by a two-day protest by outsourced workers.The outsourced workers are upset management has put out a tender for new security contractors after committing to end outsourcing.eNCA